The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Unable to pay the monthly instalments of a bank loan, Manabendra Mondal, 45, a resident of Belgachhia Road, committed suicide by hanging himself from the ceiling of his residence early on Sunday. A preliminary probe revealed that Mondal had taken the loan a year ago and failed to pay three instalments. Mondal, who is survived by his wife and two children, was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

 Indians Calcutta-Kathmandu flight, which was scheduled to take off at 1.45pm, was delayed by 30 minutes on Sunday as the pilot was apprehensive about the aircrafts weight. However, everything was found to be in order, and the flight finally took off at 2.15pm, airline officials said. 

 Tapan Das, 26, a resident of Russa Road, Jadavpur, fell from the roof of his house and died on Sunday. He was taken to MR Bangur Hospital, where he was declared dead. Police have not ruled out any foul play. 

 Razia Bibi, 26, died after falling from the third floor of a building in Topsia on Saturday. She was taken to National Medical College and Hospital, where she was declared dead. Police said she had been suffering from depression. No one was arrested.

 Seema Bibi, 27, was found hanging in her bedroom of her Metiabruz home on Saturday. Her parents-in-law have been arrested. Seemas husband and brother-in-law are absconding. Her parents alleged that she was tortured for dowry.

 The half-decomposed body of a middle-aged man was found floating in Circular Canal in Ultadanga on Sunday. Police said the body bore no marks of external injury. The body has been sent for post-mortem.

 Nabankur Banerjee and Partha Saha, students of a Barrackpore school, drowned in the Hooghly while taking a bath at Mistry Ghat on Sunday afternoon. They were joined by five other youths and a Group-D employee of the school, Bhasker Roy, who was to give them swimming lessons, police said. Local residents alleged that Bhasker was drunk.

 The Government Railway Police (GRP) on Sunday morning recovered the body of 19-year-old Rabi Shaw beside the railway tracks at Titagarh station on Sunday morning. Local residents spotted the body and informed police. Officers suspect Shaw had been been murdered somewhere else.

 Six men have been arrested on charges of robbing a few NGO officials of Rs 36.5 lakh on National Highway 34 on Monday last. Around Rs 12 lakh of the looted money has been recovered. Police said the NGO officials were on their way to deposit the money in a private bank when they were robbed in Amdanga. The arrest of the six followed a raid by a team led by the superintendent of police (North 24-Parganas) Supratim Sarkar.

